{
  "texts": [
    "Alternatively, a costsensitive framework can be incorporated to build cost-sensitive ensembles.",
    "Rather than altering the base classifier to accept costs during the learning process, cost-sensitive ensembles are designed to guide the cost minimisation procedure through the ensemble learning algorithm (López et al. 2013; Fernández et al. 2018).",
    "Galar et al. (2012) present a comprehensive taxonomy of ensemble methods for learning with imbalanced classes in their review.",
    "The authors predominantly categorise these ensemble strategies into four distinct families.",
    "The first family encompasses cost-sensitive boosting methods, while the remaining three families incorporate data preprocessing techniques and are further classified based on the ensemble learning algorithm employed, namely boosting, bagging, and hybrid ensembles."
  ]
}